replies.body:
He is likely referring to cases where a game is played after the one that triggers the 14 day ban, which then triggers a permanent suspension.

@WilliK
These cases are rare, and are not a case of a 14 day really being a perma, but rather two separate punishments issued for separate offences. It also usually requires both games to be quite bad. The chances of this happening to you are slim, though I won't say impossible. For the vast majority of punishments, the 14 day ban is issued before you can enter another game so it is not a concern.
